From 2f52bc59103c9d9cdea2bb47d0293472241cebcc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Brandon Thompson <brandon.joseph.thompson@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 15:47:54 -0700
Subject: Patch: Add OSD on brightness change from keyboard and sidebar.

Volume already flashes a bottom-of-screen OSD on any change because it binds
directly to a live Pipewire property. Backlight had no equivalent: no
hardware keybinds, and the sidebar polled brightnessctl ad hoc with no
shared state. Devices.qml now owns the laptop panel percent (alongside its
existing ddcutil external-monitor brightness) with a dedicated
panelBrightnessUserChanged signal, so the OSD flashes for a keypress or a
sidebar-fader commit but not for hypridle's silent dim/restore or a bare
sidebar open. New XF86MonBrightnessUp/Down binds call a new
`ryoku-shell backlight <up|down>` daemon verb that adjusts the panel and
notifies the pill over its existing IPC/socket path.

Tested live: hardware keys, sidebar fader, and confirmed no spurious flash
from an external brightnessctl change or from opening the sidebar alone.

